The paper discusses a machine learning approach for few-shot learning, which falls under the category of meta-learning. The paper specifically focuses on the optimization-based approach for meta-learning, which is a popular topic in the subfield of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of implicit differentiation, which is a technique used in neural networks and optimization algorithms, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on few-shot image recognition benchmarks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
